{#n167}
We learn from [p:Cicero]'s orations against [p:Verres], lib. iii. cap. 84, 92, that the price of corn in [l:Sicily] was, during the prætorship of Sacerdos, five Denarii a Modius; during that of [p:Verres], which immediately succeeded, only two Sesterces: That is, ten times lower; a presumption, or rather a proof, of the very bad state of tillage in ancient times.

